FOODBORNE DISEASE, BEAR MEAT, FATAL - SIBERIA (02)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Foodborne disease, bear meat, fatal - Siberia: RFI 971225002302
Date: Thu, 25 Dec 97 08:41:08 +03d00
From: levett@sunbeach.net
Source: Media reports

In the Siberian town of Zima, as many as 61 people, including 28 children,
were being treated at hospitals after developing food-poisoning, the
ITAR-Tass news agency said. Twelve of them were diagnosed with acute
trichinosis.
According to regional health officials, an unlicensed hunter killed the
bear and smoked the meat at his farm without submitting it for a veterinary
examination. Up to 23 kg of the tainted meat was sold in Zima. Some of the
bear meat was also sold in cities of Sayansk, Angarsk and Irkutsk, and
cases of trichinosis have also been reported in those cities."
There was no mention of deaths in the report cited above.
--
Paul N. Levett, PhD
Senior Lecturer in Microbiology
